lines.text: To dyet ranke Mindes, sicke of happinesse,

lines.text: And purge th'obstructions, which begin to stop

lines.text: (When time shall serue) to shew in Articles;

lines.text: Then, then, when there was nothing could haue stay'd

lines.text: My Father from the Breast of {% italic: Bulling brooke %};

lines.speaker: West.

lines.text: Were set on {% italic: Herford %}, whom they doted on,

lines.speaker: West.

lines.speaker: West.

lines.speaker: West.
lines.text: That argues but the shame of your offence:

lines.speaker: West.

lines.speaker: Bish.

lines.speaker: Bish.

lines.text: In sight of both our Battailes, wee may meete

lines.speaker: Bish.

lines.speaker: Bish.

lines.text: That plucking to vnfixe an Enemie,
